Metagenome-assembled genome ID: Link to metabolic reconstruction in SBML format
Determined quality level. High: completeness>90 & contamination<5 & quality score>50. Medium: completeness>50 & contamination<10 & quality score>50.
Total sequence count of all scaffolds (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaffolds/)
The sum of the (length*log(length)) of all contigs, times some constant (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/contigs/)
Total size in bp of all scaffolds (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_bp/)
Total size in bp of all contigs (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/contig_bp/)
The gap size percentage of all scaffolds (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/gap_pct/)

Given a set of scaffolds, each with its own length, the N50 count is defined as the smallest number of scaffolds whose length sum makes up half of genome size (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_n50/)
Given a set of scaffolds, the L50 is defined as the sequence length of the shortest scaffold at 50% of the total genome length (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_l50/)

Given a set of contigs, each with its own length, the N50 count is defined as the smallest number_of_contigs whose length sum makes up half of genome size (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/ctg_n50/)
Given a set of contigs, the L50 is defined as the sequence length of the shortest contig at 50% of the total genome length (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/ctg_l50/)

Given a set of scaffolds, each with its own length, the N90 count is defined as the smallest number of scaffolds whose length sum makes up 90% of genome size (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_n90/).

The L90 statistic is less than or equal to the L50 statistic; it is the length for which the collection of all scaffolds of that length or longer contains at least 90% of the sum of the lengths of all scaffolds (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_l90/)

Given a set of contigs, each with its own length, the N90 count is defined as the smallest number of contigs whose length sum makes up 90% of genome size (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/ctg_n90/)

The L90 statistic is less than or equal to the L50 statistic; it is the length for which the collection of all contigs of that length or longer contains at least 90% of the sum of the lengths of all contigs (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/ctg_l90/)
Total sequence count of scaffolds greater than 50 KB (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_n_gt50k/)
Total sequence size percentage of scaffolds greater than 50 KB (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/scaf_pct_gt50k/)
Average of GC content of all contigs (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/gc_avg/)
Standard deviation of GC content of all contigs (https://microbiomedata.github.io/nmdc-schema/gc_std/)
Total number of proteins in annotated genome (Prokka)
Total number of hypothetical proteins in annotated genome (Prokka)
Ratio of annotated proteins in genome (Prokka)

The degree of metabolic coverage indicates the modeling detail of a given reconstruction calculated by dividing the total amount of reactions by the amount of genes. Models with a 'high level of modeling detail have ratios >1, and models with a low level of detail have ratios <1 (Memote).
Number of reactions without gene-protein-reaction (GPR) associations (Memote)
Ratio of reactions without gene-protein-reaction (GPR) rules
Degrees of freedom of the stoichiometric matrix (Memote)
Maximum growth rate on the simulated minimal media
Number of carbon-containing metabolites in the simulated minimal media
Growth yield calculated as the maximum growth rate on minimal media divided by the influx of carbon atoms
